I've been coming here the better part of 15 years and always found it to be hit or miss with food and service.
The pizza and lunch prices keep bringing me back, but the service is usually just OK.
Lunch rush is always on according to the services and I've heard that as late as 7 PM there.
If you sit at the bar it does seem better, but as a government just sitting at the bar at lunch is a no no.
There also seems to be a large number of law enforcement that frequent here so no matter what time you stop by, you are in safe good company.
The parking is not the greatest, but unless you are attending an event here, you will be fine if you don't mind a little walk.
The area itself is large enough to sit plenty for most office or after work get togethers and give them little notice and they will pull tables together for you.
All in all...try the pizza and plan on running a little late for lunch, but give it a try.
If you don't like it the first time...come back...you may have a totally different experience.

